    <stitle>ANTILOCK BRAKES/TRACTION CONTROL: ROCKWELL WABCO 4 CHANNEL - TROUBLESHOOTING - ADJUSTMENT</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="adjust" graphiccount="0">
        <title>ADJUSTMENT</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Sensor</title>
            <para>Gently push the sensor in toward the tooth wheel until it bottoms out against the tooth wheel. No air
                gap is required.
            </para>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">Steer axles</emph>
                - the sensor is accessible on the in-board side of the steering knuckle.
            </para>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">Drive axle</emph>- the wheel and drum must be removed to gain access to the sensor.
            </para>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">In-board Mounted Drum Brakes</emph>- Push the sensor until it bottoms out against its
                mounting block, or bushing. DO NOT wobble the hub when installing it on the spindle or you could knock
                the sensor out of adjustment.
            </para>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
